      <tr>
        <td bgcolor='black' valign=top width='100' nowrap><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'><b>Dobi</b></font></td>
        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> If you don't care about faction, I was dreading lvl 54 and did 5 aaexp pts in feliwithe killing the first 4 guards and 2 roamers, a little down time as a lizard especially when I got regen3, as I'm not a pwr gamer I can't give you any phenominal #'s but I was very happy there. </P><P>First things first, park your pet at zone in and buff him with your augment line.. go around the first corner if a guard doesn't run into you he will walk past the first set of 2 guards you see and either stop just in front of them and turn around and walk back or walk to zone in, either way, pluck him when u can, he will single pull, shortly there will be another guard coming up there and doing the same thing..</P><P>Darkness never (very rarely) lands and one bod/pact seems to usually work for healing pet while tanking, I used the occasional "fast" heal to the pet, with drain life (or whatever its called) up to replace my mana but splurt/fire lands most of the time and eb/dark is resisted 95% of the time.</P><P>After getting the 2 pathing guards (roamers) you can go for the first 2 before the bridge, they will single pull at 52 I know, not sure about less, I always pulled the right one first, (may have something to do being able to singe pull)</P><P>Then go for the second 2 after the bridge, I found that if you just walk up and stand for about 5 seconds on the ledge  of the bridge opposite of the wall where one is, I mean right next to one on the other side of the bridge but in clear view on the other side is the guard that will agro, then you will see him agro, run back to zone in where your pet is parked and he (the guard opposite of where you were standing) will "mysteriously" pop right on top of you, take a hit for the gipper, and attract the pet, drop dot's on'm and go to the opposite wall/ledge of the bridge to get the next when the first is dead.</P><P>Rinse and repeat..</P><P>Loot: everyone drops a 2hs sword vendors for 19pp and change, the occasional pre-kunark gem and occasional FS weapon, will kill your kelethin and felwith faction though so good luck selling w/out a mule, otherwise your gonna prolly get a newb sitting there looting and getting rich off you, will make a friend for life that you'll never see again, lol</P><P>Dangers: occasionally you will get someone that realizes the hard way that they went to PoA and ruined there tunare faction and elia the pure will come a running,or <insert other guild leader mob>,  she is very tough and some of them can double atk to quad for 300+ so if you here train to zone or see someone running and looks like there getting cast on, FD or zone fast, trust me</P><P>I know my grammar/puncuation/explanation is atrocious but hopefully this will help some of you kill those pale skins..</P><P>54 Leezard Necro of Tunare</P><P>ADDED by:  Baritz Shadowreaver<BR>-Since these guards are pallies they buff themselves the second they come out, I liked to pull with Nullify Magic to get rid of the buffs.</P><P>-Use Pact of Shadow to heal your pet since the mana cost is low.</P><P>-The guards that were Dark blue to me at 52 hit for 104 max, the Light blues were around 98 max.</P><P>I used the following set up for spells, I just put them in the most comfortable order for me, use whats best for you =D<BR>1)Drain Soul<BR>2)Splurt<BR>3)Ignite Blood<BR>4)Nullify Magic<BR>5)Bond of Death<BR>6)Pact of Shadow<BR>7)Augment Death<BR>8)Lich (replace this one with Invoke Death, Arch Shielding etc.)</P><P>When I zoned in I would whip out my Encyclopedia and summon a pet, have him guard at the zone line and buff him up.<BR>Then I'd pull a roamer, usually Leguvas (sp?)</P><P>To pull I hit Nullify Magic and ran to my pet, as soon as Leg went around the corner I'd send my pet in.<BR>Next I would cast Pact of Shadow on my pet to start a sort of regen to keep his HP high, then I'd switch targets to the guard and BoD and Splurt him</P><P>At this point just sit down, as soon as Pact of Shadow wears off recast, before it finishes BoD will wear, so when Pact of Shadow wears for the second time, cast Drain soul and get back your HP, this should send the guard running.</P><P>-I've noticed when the guards HP is around 20% the guard will stop attacking and just chain cast heal on himself, this might be a good point to drain, since your pet should counter act his healing.</P><P>-I believe that the guards use Greater Healing spell but I could be wrong, also they will LoH themselves during the battle, I've never seen any sort of pattern with LoH, they just seem to mash it whenever.</P><P>Hope this helps any one bit.</P><P>Baritz Shadowreaver</P><P><BR>Edited by - Dobi on 08/10/2002  16:39:20</font></td>
