        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Drexyll</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Wow, I never knew u could single pull the front, Ive been using a different method but I THINK it yields more guards.  I invis up and run to the back area of the zone near the water and the zone to the other side of Felwithe.  I walk into the "Bait and Tackle" shop, go to the BACK of the shop (as the wandering guard is one of the mobs that magically sees through walls) pull pet and buff.</P><P>Walk outside, SOMETIMES guard Hutian will be to your left.  He is the only guard that wanders this far back.  If u dont get him right away, walk to the right and park your pet under the arch, eventually Hutian will come (always do him first).  Now, this area you are in is perfect for pulling the remaining wandering guards, 5 in all.  If you get impatient waiting for them to walk to the top of the stairs you can easily learn where to run and pull them back to your pet.</P><P>After you've killed them, you're ready to move "upstairs".  The walkway above your head (if you're down near the water) is actually linked to a tunnel thatis accessed via an false wall in the pally guild, being that we cant walts into the pally guild, I use an alternative method to get up there.  Using DMF run up the little "wall" on the right side of the steps, float across to the top of the bldg that is facing the steps.  Fromm there hang a right and go to the next rooftop.</P><P>From THERE, you can "climb" up a tree that is near the wall (this only works on the side of the tree facing the wall, so you'll have to do a 180 to get up there.)  Once on the wall turn around and run to the "overpass".  Guard Trerun walks this overpass, so make sure he's not right there, then float on over to it, and use summon companion to get your pet to you.  This area actually makes 2 rings, an inner and outter circle that go all the way around the zone.  Within you will find 4 or 5 more guards and a Lt (Something) that you can see up in a little cubby to your left if you walk into the front of the zone using the methods described in previous posts.  </P><P>Once you learn where they all are, it's pretty easy to set up a "system" here.  I usually do the bottom guards, float up to the top and run the circuit a couple of times until I've found/killed all 4 or 5 of the upper guards, by which time the bottom guards have respawned again.  Just go back to the walkway, float down to your original position, summon companion again, and start the process over again.  Using this method you should be able to kill Pally's non-stop.  </P><P>It REALLY helps to be bound at the TD firepots for this, so you can fill up on swords, poof to Neriak (or wherever) to sell off, then come right back.  Easiest spell line-up for me is pull with splurt, BoD, heal pet, rinse and repeat.</P><P>&lt;img src="http://www.onethirtyeight.com/graphics-2/cg.gif" border=0&gt;</font></td>
      </tr>
